name: THE TURBID MOON
description:
Surprise drop. Poem written and recorded by me + animation on a Odilon Redon's litography. 

My heavy arms, heavier than the night
They swing on the immensity of the turbid moon

There’s no thrust in my body
When it sleeps in a silent dream

Let me dream of another universe
So I can keep my fears hidden
Behind these dark clouds"
